+# Iteration 3: The Board Component — Implementation Plan
+
+> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.
+
+**Goal:** Build the `<Board>` component — the heart of the product — replicating `design_handoff_secondboard/reference/SecondBoard.dc.html`'s board 1:1: 8×8 grid, piece sprites, flip-aware coordinate labels, last-move highlight, classification badges, the brilliant-move pulse ring, the best-move arrow, and the single-step piece-slide animation. Per README §11 step 3 / LOGIC.md §8 step 3.
+
+**Architecture:** Pure, unit-testable logic modules under `src/lib/board/` (piece-sprite registry, board-geometry math ported verbatim from `reference/logic/view-math.js`, a pure square-list builder ported from the reference's `buildBoard()`, a pure position-diff function, and an imperative DOM slide-animation function) feed two small Svelte 5 components: `BoardSquare.svelte` (one square: background, last-move tint, brilliant ring, coordinate labels, piece, badge) composed by `Board.svelte` (grid assembly, best-move arrow SVG overlay, and an `$effect` that triggers the slide animation on single-step ply changes). A temporary, explicitly-labeled dev-fixtures harness (ported verbatim from `reference/logic/chess-mock.js` + `reference/logic/data.js`, **not shipped as product code**) is wired into the existing `+page.svelte` screen-switcher placeholder so the component can be pixel-verified against `reference/screens/2-game-review-analysis-tab.png` / `3-game-review-review-tab.png` before the real Game Review screen (Iteration 4) replaces it.
+
+**Tech Stack:** SvelteKit 2.x + Svelte 5 (runes), TypeScript strict, Vite's `?url` asset-import suffix for bundling the 12 piece SVGs offline, Vitest + `@testing-library/svelte` (jsdom) for component tests, plain Vitest for pure-function unit tests.
+
+## Global Constraints
+
+- **Zero visual deviation** — every color/size/radius/gap/shadow/animation value in this plan is copied verbatim from `design_handoff_secondboard/README.md` §4.4/§5/§6.3, `LOGIC.md` §2, and the literal markup/JS extracted from `reference/SecondBoard.dc.html` (quoted inline in each task below). Do not approximate or "clean up" a value.
+- **`psize` is vestigial** — the reference's `buildBoard(pos, opts)` accepts a `psize` option (58 on the main board, 24/40 on mini/training boards) but never wires it into any generated style string; piece/square size is purely a function of the 8×8 grid cell. Do not add a `pieceSize` prop to `Board`/`BoardSquare` — it would have no reference behavior to replicate.
+- **Board renders no eval bar.** README §8.2's module layout lists `Board` and `EvalBar` as siblings under `board/`/`components/`; the eval bar is a separate component that lands with the Game Review screen (Iteration 4). This iteration's `<Board>` is exactly: grid, sprites, coordinates, flip, last-move highlight, badges, brilliant ring, best-move arrow, slide animation.
+- **`chess-mock.js` (SAN→position engine) is a MOCK per LOGIC.md's explicit warning ("⚠ THIS IS A MOCK... In the REAL app you MUST NOT ship this").** It is ported in this plan **only** into a file clearly named and commented as temporary/dev-only (`src/lib/board/dev-fixtures.ts`), used solely to feed the visual-verification harness. Iteration 4 replaces it with real Rust `pgn` data and this file is expected to be deleted then.
+- **Svelte 5 runes only** — `$props()`/`$derived`/`$state`/`$effect`, per `svelte.config.js`'s forced runes mode.
+- **TypeScript strict mode; no `any`** (enforced by `eslint.config.js`'s `@typescript-eslint/no-explicit-any: error`).
